##The man who pulled pregnant women out of the fear of an epidemic: the birth of a newborn is a light that shines into our hearts | in depth coverage

MICRO-SIGNAL BQSHENYIDU

Beijing Youth Daily reports from the official public number

Reporter / Tong Xiaoyu intern reporter / Lin Yiqiao

Editor / Edward Shek, Jianhua Song

Volunteers take pregnant women to the entrance of hospital

About 10,000 babies are born every month in Wuhan. After the outbreak of the epidemic, part of the medical and nursing staff of the hospital's obstetrics and Gynecology Department was transferred to support the fever out-patient and emergency departments. Routine examinations and out-patient services for pregnant and lying-in women were limited. A large number of patients with fever were admitted to public hospitals at the same time, it also puts pregnant women at varying risk of infection.

##Under all sorts of epidemic prevention measures, meet the new life brought by tension, anxiety is magnified, at the same time, pregnant and lying-in women also face travel difficulties, difficult to check the actual problem.

In the immediate aftermath of the outbreak, teams of volunteers, including obstetricians and gynaecologists, psychologists, lactation specialists, full time mothers and drivers, were set up to watch over newborns.

When the news of a new baby came, there was jubilation in the crowd. "It was like a light in my heart, " one volunteer said.

Deng Yun Volunteer Group of consultants are mostly gynecologists, lactation division, lactation guidance and other professionals

Back Up

At two o'clock in the morning, Gansu Wuwei gynecologist Zhang Dong's mobile phone tip has been ringing wechat.

A pregnant woman in Hubei Province, 35 weeks and 4 days pregnant, had abdominal pain for half an hour and asked for help in the group. Zhang asked about the frequency of pain, confirmed that she is not irregular contractions in labor, but pregnant women or worry about whether the problem.

Zhang Dong let her attention in 10 minutes whether there are 2-3 times abdominal pain, waiting, the group of another pregnant 37 weeks pregnant mother, and sent help.

In the traffic-controlled city of Hubei Province, each pain has left parturient mothers anxious and unable to sleep, for fear of going to the hospital late at night.

The Free Consultation Group for pregnant and lying-in women in Hubei was founded by Han Lei, an obstetrician and gynecologist at the maternal and child health hospital in Zunyi, Guizhou Province. At present, there are 3000 pregnant and lying-in women from Hubei Province.

On the eve of the Lunar New Year, Han Lei called a friend in the same field in Wuhan and learned that most of the doctors in his department of Obstetrics and gynecology had been called away to support fever clinics and emergency departments, resulting in the inability of some pregnant women to carry out regular checkups and outpatient clinics, the large number of fever patients admitted to public hospitals in the same period also exposed pregnant women to varying degrees of risk of infection.

Han Lei took the situation to his academic community and called on obstetricians and gynecologists from other regions to help Hubei doctors triage to ensure maximum maternal and fetal safety. On the 24th, parturient women and doctors joined in succession, and the consultation group quickly expanded to 12.

After the outbreak, such consultation group is not a minority, obstetricians, psychologists, lactation division, full-time mothers, they form a variety of teams to support the birth of Hubei pregnant women.

Deng Yun, an obstetrician and gynecologist, is also an internationally certified lactation specialist. Her team has been working on the project since the beginning of the Lunar New Year, and three groups are now receiving online counseling for pregnant women.

Deng Yun's team targeted pregnant women in Hubei Province. There were more than 40 volunteers in the group. More than 30 of them were experienced breast milk instructors. There were also more than a dozen doctors from the departments of obstetrics and gynecology, pediatrics and psychology at various tertiary hospitals. "They all have three to five years of experience, some of them are certified by international lactation consultants. "

Like Han Lei, he launched an initiative among medical professionals and soon received responses from more than 200 people. Within 24 hours, the team was assembled, "like an urgent self-help campaign. ".

Even if the birth is successful, there will be various problems during the lactation period. "For example, if a newborn baby has a stuffy nose, the mother is very worried and will always ask if she should go to a hospital, " Deng said. "In fact, the baby can be handled with the guidance and intervention of an online doctor, and does not need to risk going to a hospital. "

One of the expectant mothers in the group was hospitalized and quarantined because of a suspected infection. Deng Yun introduced, "she does not know how to go to childbirth, choose what kind of hospital, now many hospitals obstetrics is in a state of shutdown, we will help her communication fixed point medical institutions, contact beds. "

From 8:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. , each day, three volunteers work in three clusters, handling questions and counseling. So far, the group has benefited more than 1,000 people.

Thank you cards Deng Yun received in the group

Talk to me

Support is not just physical, it's psychological.

Two weeks after giving birth is the peak period for postpartum depression. Many new mothers, are confused about what they don't know, don't know how to take care of their children, many pregnant women lose sleep at night, and the epidemic magnifies their anxiety.

Wu Xuejuan joined the "Baby Care Program" on Feb. 6. The group's volunteers come from all walks of life. They pay attention to the health of pregnant and lying-in women as well as their emotional guidance.

Guo Diqing, a volunteer, remembers that more than 100 consultants came into the group on the first night. "Most of them were pregnant women at 38 or 39 weeks, each with different needs. " Neither Wu Xuejuan nor Guo Diqing expected that the group would be so large, "almost a dozen more people are added every day and there are now nearly 300 people in the group. "

Stay-at-home mother Wu Xuejuan has given birth three times, the youngest child is five years old. She joked that her volunteer work was "chatting" and that "in times of crisis, not being able to get a prenatal check-up on time or anything else makes mothers more anxious, and they always worry, 'what if something happens to my baby? ' "

Apart from taking care of her youngest child, Ms. Wu spends most of her time answering questions from pregnant women. "At this time, they have to stay at home all the time. What they need is an outlet to talk. "

The babywatch volunteers were matched one-on-one, in seven groups, each with its own docking group. In addition to docking pregnant and lying-in women, as a group leader, Guo is also responsible for the distribution of personnel within the group, problem summary and feedback.

"The most important thing is to solve their anxiety. On the one hand, they are afraid of the virus outside. On the other hand, they don't know if they can go to the hospital to give birth. " Every morning, Guo Diqing sends messages to the pregnant women she connects with, ask about their status and mood.

She would listen carefully to their lives, some pregnant women at home boring, Guo Diqing will pull them to the reading group, "let them have something to do. ". We brainstorming, formed their own list of books, parenting, psychological aspects have, recently someone recommended "Dear Andre" , "accompany a heart grow up" .

Guo, who majored in psychology, trained in Wuhan and is now stuck in her hometown in Shiyan. Sometimes, when a pregnant woman's cry for help is close to a complaint, with a strong negative emotion, Guo "filters out the words and tries to guide her partner with her own optimism. "

Volunteers turn down red envelopes from mothers'families

Prenatal examination

The volunteers were sponging up their time to help the women, but the work didn't always go smoothly, with initial fuss, maternal distrust and lack of understanding from the volunteer's family.

Deng Yun and team members have been looking for better ways to connect with pregnant and lying-in women, and have been regularly discussing various cases and problems encountered in the group, "We also hope that the volunteers will be in a better state to serve by letting go of their emotions during the comeback. "

Zhang joined the first free consultation group for pregnant and lying-in women on January 23. When she returned to Gansu from Shenzhen on January 27, the community asked her to stay home from her husband for 14 days. With more time, she applied to work with pregnant women in both groups. Zhang Dong eats a meal when the mobile phone does not leave the hand, the midnight mobile phone information unceasingly.

A few days later, the National Health Commission of the press conference, the reporter asked about the epidemic area of maternal and obstetric difficulties. "What you're doing is meaningful, " the husband said, turning to Zhang. Since then, the husband has taken on all the housework at home, giving Zhang more time to serve the parturient.

Among the many consultations, there are a lot of questions about the prenatal examination. "The biggest concern for pregnant women is that they will not be able to get their check-ups on time, which will increase maternal and neonatal mortality. For example, a pregnant woman would have to be screened for NT at week 12, after which time she would not be able to do so. We told expectant mothers that no matter what, they should find a way to do a b-ultrasound at this time. This is the bottom line, han Lei said.

Every two days, volunteers from the Wuhan left-behind Mothers Support Union will call hospitals in Wuhan to confirm the program and provide accurate information for pregnant and lying-in women in Wuhan.

Qing Qing, a pregnant woman from Hubei Province, returned home with her husband to Henan Province for the Lunar New Year holiday when she was 13 weeks pregnant. Because of the epidemic, the home road closure, do not let Hubei people into the city, Qingqing tried to go to the city several times to do NT prenatal examination were intercepted back, until the 15th week, she can not do NT ultrasound.

Hubei Pregnant Women Free Consultation Group of volunteers remind Qingqing, 16 weeks of down's screening must not be missed.

The vehicles used to transport the women are sterilized, and the drivers have built their own quarantine

PARTURIENT

Four pregnant women in the baby watch group have given birth safely.

The first production of publicity, is in the "baby-watching program" set up the first time into the group. At the time, Zhang Yang was a month away from her due date, but she was unable to attend her doctor's appointment.

At 5:30 am on February 6th, Zhang Yang began seeing red, 14 days ahead of her due date. Because the microsomia examination showed the fetus in transverse position, Zhang Yang needed a caesarean section.

Zhang Yang remembers that it was raining in Wuhan that day. Her husband drove her to Hubei Maternal and Child Health Hospital. The atmosphere in the hospital was more solemn than usual. By 6 p.m. , Zhang finished all the tests and prepared for a Cesarean section. "The wait was especially long and intense during the outbreak. "

After the birth, Zhang Yang in the group talked about the situation in the hospital in detail, before we are most worried about is to go to the hospital after what to do? The information that Zhang Yang brings back, let the mood of a lot of anxious mother stabilizes.

Zhang Yang sees the group as his own "organization, " and "you feel like you're not alone, that you're not the only one going through these special situations. "

Not everyone makes it from home to the hospital as smoothly as Zhang Yang. Late at night, messages sent by pregnant women often pull another group of volunteers from the "W big Wuhan Emergency Rescue Team" .

The group has a four-person convoy that transports pregnant women in Wuhan to the hospital. New Life often does not arrive as planned, with all sorts of contingencies and a reliance on volunteer convoys for families with travel difficulties.

There are only four volunteer drivers for pregnant women, who rotate around the clock to support the 220 parturients in the alliance group who are over 35 weeks pregnant and who are ready to race behind the wheel.

To get her to the hospital as quickly as possible, volunteer Wang Ziyi never takes off her clothes when she goes to bed. The volunteer driver, Li Wenjian, has never slept before 1 am.

The mother, Li Xue, is due to give birth on Feb. 22, and she has been in constant pain since 4 a.m. on Feb. 12. At this time, Wuhan Public Transport has been suspended, Li Xue contact 120 emergency center, 120 emergency vehicles have just picked up the new severe pneumonia patients, need the whole car after disinfection can be seen. Li Xue's water broke before the ambulance arrived. At 4:32 in the morning, she calls out to a group of expectant mothers.

A few minutes later, Wang Ziyi to Li Xue confirmed the location of the community, contact information, accompany the number of information, at the same time contact Li Wenjian. At 5:04, Li Wenjian received Li Xue in front of the nearest department store.

Li Wenjian's car speed has been maintained at the top speed limit, 5:30 pm, Li Xue and his wife were sent to Hubei Province maternal and Child Health Hospital. For each other's safety, Li Xue did not shake hands with the driver when they got off the bus, and nodded to each other.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A mother gave birth with the help of a volunteer

Newborn baby

After delivering Li Xue, Li Wenjian disinfected the whole vehicle, then lay back in bed at seven in the morning. Two hours later, he had to get up and stand by again.

To ensure the safety of pregnant and lying-in women, delivery drivers also use a variety of ways to give their own car "upgrade. ". Wang Zhen uses cardboard and cellophane to separate the front and back of the car. Every time he goes home, he sprays disinfectant water all over the car. He worries about the smell, which will make the pregnant woman uncomfortable. He also breathes for 15 to 20 minutes on the roadside.

Team leader Wang Ziyi, the current team of 4 volunteer drivers to undertake the 13 districts of Wuhan 220 pregnant women in Labor and delivery work. In order to ensure maternal safety, the driver of the high-level protection, the delivery of a parturient woman means that the consumption of a protective clothing.

"War epidemic" more than a month, Wang Ziyi every night from 23:00 to 6:00 on the next day in the group of Parturient, for fear of missing every call for help. The News of a new baby's birth is the one that can instantly relieve the feeling of fatigue.

At 10 pm on February 22, Li Wenjian and Wang Ziyi received a message from Li Xue's husband, "thank you for giving birth at 7 pm today. ".

Up to now, Zhang Dong has to answer more than 200 questions from pregnant and lying-in women every day in the free consultation group. As a result of her help, a breathing difficulties in hospital in time to give birth to two daughters, it is Zhang Dong home isolation since the happiest thing.

On February 11, seven mothers in the group of the Wuhan left-behind Pregnant Mothers Support Union reported good news. They joked that all the babies born on February 11 would surely go to "211" university. Tsutsu, a volunteer, said hearing the news of the birth during the outbreak opened her heart "like something was flowing out and some light was coming in" .

To protect the privacy of the interviewees, Zhang Dong was given a false name
